==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nuthatch
<hw>Nut"hatch`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>nuthake</ets>. See 2d <er>Hack</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of several species of birds of the genus <gen>Sitta</gen>,
as the European species (<spn>Sitta Europaea</spn>). The
<stype>white-breasted nuthatch</stype> (<spn>Sitta Carolinensis</spn>),
the <stype>red-breasted nuthatch</stype> (<spn>Sitta Canadensis</spn>),
the <stype>pygmy nuthatch</stype> (<spn>Sitta pygmaea</spn>), and
others, are American.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nuthook</ent>⟦br⟧
